<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>ALTERNATOR: LEECE NEVILLE AND PRESTOLITE JN SERIES - COMPONENT TESTING - ROTOR TEST</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="test" graphiccount="2">
        <title>ROTOR TEST</title>
        <para>The rotor should be checked for grounds and proper coil resistance with an ohmmeter.</para>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">With the ohmmeter connected between the rotor shaft and either slip ring, no reading
                (infinity) should be obtained. If an ohmmeter reading other than infinity is obtained, the rotor coil is
                grounded and the rotor must be replaced (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0802014">Figure 14</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f0802014" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g0802014" filename="../figg08/G0802014.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="272px" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Rotor Test</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Check rotor coil resistance by connecting the ohmmeter across the two slip rings (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0802015">Figure 15</hotlnk>). The resistance of the rotor should be within the
                following limits:
            </para>
            <figure id="f0802015" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g0802015" filename="../figg08/G0802015.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="272px" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Check Rotor Coil Resistance</caption>
            </figure>
            <table id="hl0802002">
                <title>Rotor Coil Resistance Table</title>
                <tgroup cols="2">
                    <colspec colname="1" colwidth="2.20in"/>
                    <colspec colname="2" colwidth="2.38in"/>
                    <tbody>
                        <row rowsep="0">
                            <entry colname="1" align="center">
                                <para>0310JN</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="2" align="center">
                                <para>4.9 - 5.5 Ohms</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row rowsep="0">
                            <entry colname="1" align="center">
                                <para>0410JN</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="2" align="center">
                                <para>2.3 - 2.7 Ohms</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row rowsep="0">
                            <entry colname="1" align="center">
                                <para>0510JN</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="2" align="center">
                                <para>1.85 - 2.0 Ohms</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row rowsep="0">
                            <entry colname="1" align="center">
                                <para>0610JN</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="2" align="center">
                                <para>1.85 - 2.0 Ohms</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row rowsep="0">
                            <entry colname="1" align="center">
                                <para>0810JN</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="2" align="center">
                                <para>1.9 - 2.3 Ohms</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row rowsep="0">
                            <entry colname="1" align="center">
                                <para>0910JN</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="2" align="center">
                                <para>1.9 - 2.3 Ohms</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </table>
            <para>If resistance reading is higher than values given in chart above, then unsolder slip ring lead
                connections from rotor coil leads and measure resistance across the coil leads. If resistance is still
                too high, then rotor assembly is defective and must be replaced. If resistance reading is within values
                shown, then resolder slip ring leads and check resistance across the two slip rings. If resistance is
                still above values shown, then slip ring assembly must be replaced.
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
